description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Second Step &lt;/strong&gt;is a leading mental health charity in the South West offering housing, support and hope to thousands of people with mental health and other problems.  Our goal is to inspire hope and deliver change for everybody and every community we work with.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support workers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 x 37 hours&lt;/strong&gt; (5 days per week)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type        &lt;/strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary             &lt;/strong&gt;£19,597 - £21,404&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location         &lt;/strong&gt;Bristol&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Supported Housing service provides low and medium tenancy related support to people with a range of complex needs including homelessness, drug and alcohol misuse, re-offending and mental health issues who require support to progress towards more independent living.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service operates a rota to provide extended support between 18:00 and 20:00 Monday, Wednesday and Friday, and 10:00 to 14:00 on Saturday which staff are expected to be a part of.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for providing recovery focussed support to people, promoting independence and supporting vulnerable people in developing move on and recovery plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a minimum of one years experience of working with people with complex needs in the social housing field. Experience and understanding of working with people with multiple needs, homelessness, mental health or drug/alcohol dependency is essential. Just as important is your ability to work as part of a team with your support and housing colleagues&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work in a recovery focused psychologically informed way (PIE) and you will receive comprehensive training, regular supervision and be part of team reflective practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full driving license and access to transport is essential as the post involves travel around the Bristol area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: &lt;/strong&gt;            8th Nov 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview dates(s)     &lt;/strong&gt;11th Nov 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Second Step is committed to Equal Opportunities and welcomes applicants from all sections of the community and from people who have personal experience of using mental health services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
